feat: A new feature.

fix: A bug fix.

docs: Documentation changes.

style: Code style changes (whitespace, formatting, semicolons, etc. â€“ does not affect code behavior).

refactor: A code refactoring (no behavior change).

test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests.

chore: Maintenance tasks, build process changes, auxiliary tools, etc. (neither a feature, a fix, nor a refactor).

perf: A code change that improves performance.

build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies.

ci: Changes to CI configuration files and scripts.